âš™ï¸ How I Deployed the Project (Steps)
1ï¸âƒ£ Launched EC2 Instance

OS: Amazon Linux

Connected using EC2 Instance Connect

2ï¸âƒ£ Installed Docker
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install docker -y
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker

3ï¸âƒ£ Created Flask App

Wrote app.py using Flask
#code --:

from flask import Flask, request, render_template_string
from datetime import datetime

app = Flask(__name__)

HTML = """
<h2>Task Manager (Docker)</h2>
<form method="POST">
  <input type="text" name="task" required>
  <button type="submit">Save</button>
</form>
<p>{{ message }}</p>
"""

@app.route("/", methods=["GET","POST"])
def home():
    message = ""
    if request.method == "POST":
        task = request.form.get("task")
        time = datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
        with open("tasks.txt","a") as f:
            f.write(f"[{time}] {task}\n")
        message = "Task saved!"
    return render_template_string(HTML, message=message)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5000)

website code 
App runs on port 5000

4ï¸âƒ£ Created requirements.txt
flask
here we tell which Dependency we have to use

Purpose:
To tell Docker which Python libraries are needed.

5ï¸âƒ£ Created Dockerfile

FROM python:3.9-slim

WORKDIR /app

COPY requirement.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirement.txt

COPY app.py .

EXPOSE 5000

CMD ["python", "app.py"]

   Dockerfile is used to control container and install dependency .
Purpose:
To tell Docker how to build the application container.

6ï¸âƒ£ Built Docker Image
docker build -t flask-task-app .
here build is used beacuse it search for Dockerfile and run it

7ï¸âƒ£ Ran Docker Container
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name flask_app flask-task-app

8ï¸âƒ£ Opened Website in Browser
http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:5000
